snippet.textDisplay:
I was a wrestling fan for as long as I can remember. One of my first memories of being alive was watching Kevin Von Erich throw one of his picture perfect dropkicks in WCCW. During the Attitude Era, I would not work on Monday or Thursday nights. Those were my nights off, because those were wrestling nights. I was die hard. I had periods where I would not watch so often, but I would always come back.

Bad programming was part of the reason I stopped watching. Part of it was being too busy, family, music, etc.

But the Benoit thing, that's when the portion of my inner self that was devoted to wrestling became irreparably damaged. I could never look at it the same way, or feel the same way, ever again.

Everyone can have their own reactions, but that's mine.
snippet.textOriginal:

I had periods where I would not watch so often, but I would always come back.
